The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring April 22, 2010, as Earth Day. It reflects on the history of Earth Day and the progress made in environmental protection over the past four decades. The article emphasizes the importance of being good stewards of the planet and encourages all Americans to participate in programs and activities that protect the environment and contribute to a sustainable future. The proclamation also highlights the Obama administration's investments in clean energy and clean water infrastructure and the commitment to passing comprehensive energy and climate legislation. The article concludes by urging future generations to continue the cause of Earth Day and ensure a cleaner and healthier planet for the future.